The paper is about a content-based multimedia information retrieval system, which involves searching for objects across different media types such as images, audio, videos, and 3D models. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Multimedia (cs.MM), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Deep Learning (cs.DL), and Databases (cs.DB). Among these, cs.MM and cs.IR are the most likely categories as they directly relate to multimedia retrieval and information retrieval, respectively. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques for feature extraction, which makes cs.DL a likely category. The use of computer vision techniques for image and video analysis further supports the inclusion of cs.CV. Finally, the paper discusses the design of a web-based user interface, which could be relevant to cs.DB.
